rules.Title: Fireplaces included in gross floor area (GFA)

Qualifiers.Scope: Counting of fireplaces toward gross floor area (GFA).
Qualifiers.Applicability: All fireplaces associated with a building, regardless of configuration or design.
Qualifiers.Exclusions: Fireplaces not connected to the house are treated as accessory structures per R4.

fireplace_is_connected_to_house.description: Whether the fireplace is physically connected to the main building.

counting_method.description: Each qualifying fireplace is included one time toward GFA.

Conditions.logic: IF fireplace_is_connected_to_house == true THEN include fireplace area in GFA (count once).

Exceptions.text: IF fireplace_is_connected_to_house == false THEN treat as accessory structure (see R4).
Exceptions.effect: Use FAR/lot coverage rules in R4; GFA treatment not stated here.

Relationships.notes: General statement is complemented by specifics for chimneys (R3) and detached fireplaces (R4).

Ambiguities: “Counted one time” is not defined: whether per fireplace element, per floor, or per building is unclear.
GFA treatment for detached fireplaces is implied to be excluded but not explicitly stated.

rules.Title: Sheds, planters, and other projections over 5 feet count toward GFA

Qualifiers.Scope: Counting of exterior projections/structures toward gross floor area (GFA).
Qualifiers.Applicability: Sheds, planters, and other projections; includes miscellaneous appendages such as tool sheds, equipment enclosures, play houses, etc.
Qualifiers.Exclusions: Items 5 feet or less in height do not count toward GFA under this rule.

element_height.description: Height of the element measured vertically.

height_threshold.description: Minimum height above which the element counts toward GFA.

Conditions.logic: IF element_height > 5 ft THEN include element in GFA.
Counting is independent of configuration or design.

overlaps_with: R5 (location restrictions for appendages/noise equipment; separate from GFA counting)

Ambiguities: “Other projections” and “miscellaneous appendages” are broad and not exhaustively defined.

rules.Title: Chimney counting toward GFA with upper-floor exemption; buttresses count once

Qualifiers.Scope: Counting of chimneys and buttresses toward gross floor area (GFA).
Qualifiers.Applicability: All configurations of fireplaces, chimneys, and buttresses.
Qualifiers.Exclusions: Chimneys located on upper floors are excluded from GFA counting.

floor_level.description: Building floor on which the chimney is located (e.g., ground/first floor, upper floors).

counting_method.description: For qualifying features (except upper-floor chimneys), include once toward GFA.

Conditions.logic: IF feature_type == 'chimney' AND floor_level is in upper floors THEN EXCLUDE from GFA.
IF feature_type in ['fireplace','chimney','buttress'] AND NOT (feature_type == 'chimney' AND floor_level is in upper floors) THEN include in GFA (count once).

Relationships.notes: Diagram text introduces a specific exemption for upper-floor chimneys that narrows the general counting rule.

Ambiguities: “Upper floors” is not precisely defined; interpret as any story above the first/ground floor.
“Count once” meaning is not operationally defined (e.g., per feature vs per building).

rules.Title: Detached fireplaces treated as accessory structures; FAR and lot coverage counting

Qualifiers.Scope: Classification and area counting of fireplaces not connected to the house.
Qualifiers.Applicability: Fireplaces not connected to the principal building.
Qualifiers.Exclusions: Attached fireplaces are covered by R1/R3.

fireplace_is_connected_to_house.description: Determines whether to apply accessory structure rules.

structure_area.description: Plan area of the detached fireplace/accessory structure.

FAR_area_threshold.description: Detached fireplace counts toward FAR only if its area exceeds this threshold.

lot_coverage_rule.description: Detached fireplaces count toward lot coverage regardless of size.

Conditions.logic: IF fireplace_is_connected_to_house == false THEN classify as accessory structure.
IF fireplace_is_connected_to_house == false AND structure_area > 120 sq ft THEN include in FAR.
IF fireplace_is_connected_to_house == false THEN include in lot coverage (regardless of structure_area).

cross_references: R5 (location restrictions may apply to accessory structures where defined as appendages)

Ambiguities: GFA applicability for detached fireplaces is not explicitly stated; implied exclusion.
Measurement method for structure_area (e.g., footprint vs total enclosed area) is not specified.

rules.Title: Location restriction: appendages and noise-producing equipment not allowed in required yards

Qualifiers.Scope: Location of certain exterior elements relative to required yards.
Qualifiers.Applicability: Miscellaneous appendages (e.g., tool sheds, equipment enclosures, play houses, similar items) and noise-producing equipment.
Qualifiers.Exclusions: Not specified; any exceptions to yard restrictions are not provided in the text.

element_type.description: Type of item subject to yard location restriction.

location_in_required_yard.description: Whether the item is located within any required yard.

prohibited_zone.description: Zone where these items may not be located.

Conditions.logic: IF location_in_required_yard == true AND element_type in ['tool_shed','equipment_enclosure','play_house','other_appendage','noise_producing_equipment'] THEN NOT PERMITTED.

overlaps_with: R2 (GFA counting of appendages > 5 ft is separate from location prohibition)

Ambiguities: “Required yards” is not defined here; must reference zoning definitions.
“Noise-producing equipment” is not defined; may require separate standards to classify.

rules.Title: Prohibition on new wood-burning fireplaces (City of Palo Alto)

Qualifiers.Scope: Construction of new wood-burning fireplaces within the City of Palo Alto.
Qualifiers.Applicability: New wood-burning fireplaces after the effective ordinance date.
Qualifiers.Exclusions: Possible exceptions per Chapter 9.06.030 (details not provided in the excerpt).

jurisdiction.description: City where the project is located; must be Palo Alto for this rule to apply.

is_new_construction.description: Whether the fireplace is newly constructed (as opposed to existing).

ordinance_effective_year.description: Year the ordinance was passed; exact effective date not specified.

code_reference.description: Chapter containing details and possible exceptions.

Conditions.logic: IF jurisdiction == 'Palo Alto' AND fireplace_type == 'wood-burning' AND is_new_construction == true THEN PROHIBITED.

Exceptions.effect: Project may be permitted under specified exceptions; details not provided here.

relies_on: External legal text: Palo Alto Municipal Code Chapter 9.06.030
overlaps_with: R1 (fireplace counting) in the sense that prohibited items would not be counted if not permitted.
Relationships.notes: This is a separate prohibition ordinance; counting rules only apply where installation is otherwise permitted.

Ambiguities: Exact effective date in 2000 and retroactivity to permits filed before enactment are not specified.
Scope by occupancy type (residential vs commercial) is not stated.
